    "text": "Could have been? I mean, this is pretty visionary, and I feel like we just got there.\n\nWith the data-urls we finally have model-view independence for serializable stuff, combine with WebSocket for multi-client applications. (Caveat that I'm not working with distributed object programming, which sounds like it's just for safely mutating the objects.) Or are you pointing in the direction of embedding other languages, e.g. clingo ASP via WASM?\n\nThe claim of ES6 to myriad useful forms is quite strong. Here I thought we'd magically emerged from the bad old jQuery days. But seeing ES6's full lineage in <https://futureofcoding.slack.com/archives/C5U3SEW6A/p1722224575586259|Calculating Empires> was revelatory.\n\nUniversal readership! Hahaha. The hypertexts were so successful that now we have too much of a good thing.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1726673524.756939",
    "parent_user_id": "UC2A2ARPT",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "gLk75",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Could have been? I mean, this is pretty visionary, and I feel like we just got there.\n\nWith the data-urls we finally have model-view independence for serializable stuff, combine with WebSocket for multi-client applications. (Caveat that I'm not working with distributed object programming, which sounds like it's just for safely mutating the objects.) Or are you pointing in the direction of embedding other languages, e.g. clingo ASP via WASM?\n\nThe claim of ES6 to myriad useful forms is quite strong. Here I thought we'd magically emerged from the bad old jQuery days. But seeing ES6's full lineage in "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://futureofcoding.slack.com/archives/C5U3SEW6A/p1722224575586259",
                "text": "Calculating Empires"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " was revelatory.\n\nUniversal readership! Hahaha. The hypertexts were so successful that now we have too much of a good thing."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
